                "s2_paper_id": "2c508a22fd9a22e5a9c8af6c2693dcd6e6d3c5ac",
                "title": "Other Stories to Tell: Recovery Scholarship and the Infrastructure for Digital Humanities",
                "year": 2025,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 0,
                "abstract": "Other Stories To Tell is the final report of the Commission on Fostering and Sustaining Diverse Digital Scholarship, a group of 21 leading scholars, librarians, archivists, publishers, and University leaders convened by ACLS to analyze the current challenges in providing equitable access to the creation and sustainability of digital resources and projects related to social and racial justice.\n\nThis comprehensive study highlights successful and failed approaches in addressing both the precarity and the potential of community-built projects, as well as those that have not been created with the benefit of subsidy from a college or university.",
